# Gitleaks Ignore File
# Feature: 002-gitlab-security-pipeline
# Purpose: Exclude false positives from secret detection
#
# This file tells Gitleaks to ignore specific files or patterns that contain
# example/placeholder secrets in documentation or test files.
#
# Documentation: https://github.com/gitleaks/gitleaks#gitleaksignore

# ==============================================================================
# Documentation Examples (T023)
# ==============================================================================
# Documentation files often contain example API keys for illustration
# These are safe to ignore as they're clearly marked as examples

# Markdown documentation files with example keys
docs/**/*.md
*.md:EXAMPLE_API_KEY
*.md:AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE

# README files with placeholder credentials
README.md
CONTRIBUTING.md

# ==============================================================================
# Test Files
# ==============================================================================
# Test files intentionally contain fake secrets for validating the scanner
# These should be excluded from blocking the pipeline

# Test commit files (used for TDD validation)
tests/security/test-commits/**/*

# Expected results JSON files
tests/security/expected-results/**/*.json

# ==============================================================================
# Configuration Examples
# ==============================================================================
# Configuration template files often show example values

*.example
*.template
.env.example
.env.template
config.example.*
config.template.*

# ==============================================================================
# False Positive Patterns
# ==============================================================================
# Specific patterns that are known false positives

# Lines containing "EXAMPLE" in the secret (documentation placeholders)
*:*EXAMPLE*

# Lines explicitly marked as examples or placeholders
*:# Example:*
*:// Example:*
*:<!-- Example:*
